main event: Unidentified objects were found in a photo of the moon taken on April 22, 1969, in Joppatowne, Maryland.
interesting points: The objects in the photo are described as likely being caused by photographic errors, The quality of the imagery was too low to permit specific identification of the anomalies, The report concluded that the anomalies were most probably a combination of debris and reflections within the optical system, The negative of the photograph was reportedly lost shortly after analysis, The report was authored by Lt Col Hector Quintanilla, who was the Chief of the Aerial Phenomena Office at the time.
sighted object: unidentified anomalies in a photograph of the moon
